<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-15-0712 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper considers demand for commercial energy in developing countries.In particular, it seeks to understand the nature of the demand for oil,set against developments in other commercial fuels, insofar as the demandwill impact on the world oil market. To do this, the paper seeks to answerfour broad questions, namely, what is the current and projected demandin developing countries? Are there substantial variations amongst developingcountries in projected demand? Do different price structures for hydrocarbonssignificantly alter energy opportunities? What implications does thedemand for commercial energy in developing countries have for developedcountries? With 29 refs.</TEXT></DOC>